    bbox_to_anchor=(.5, 1), ncol=15, title=None, frameon=False,
)

Inferenece : The scatter plot of the car crashes dataset suggests that there is no clear linear correlation between alcohol consumption and the total number of crashes, with data points scattered across a wide range of values.

In [9]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
sns.boxplot(x="alcohol", y="total", data=dataset)
plt.title("Boxplot of Alcohol vs. Total Crashes")
plt.xlabel("Alcohol Consumption")
plt.ylabel("Total Crashes")
plt.show()

Inference: The boxplot illustrates the relationship between alcohol consumption and total crashes, showing potential outliers

The countplot displays the frequency of each car type in the dataset.
